    "subtype": "weapon",
    "text": "This kobold wire is thin and hard to see, making it perfect for an ambush. The wielder flicks one handle around a vulnerable spot so that it serves as a catch for the wire, then yanks the other handle back, pulling the wire tight and inflicting painful lacerations. The function and name come from a wire-based trap called a \u201cslow fang.\u201d",
    "traits": [
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 159,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "uncommon"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "f31704572455b8d77a8bd97c0045fde6",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "links": [
          {
            "alt": "Recall Knowledge",
            "aonid": 26,
            "game-obj": "Actions",
            "name": "Recall Knowledge",
            "type": "link"
          }
        ],
        "name": "Uncommon",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 11",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 11",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 11,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Something of uncommon rarity requires special training or comes from a particular culture or part of the world. Some character choices give access to uncommon options, and the GM can choose to allow access for anyone. Less is known about uncommon creatures than common creatures. They typically can't be summoned. The DC of Recall Knowledge checks related to these creature is increased by 2.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 170,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "52e96f4918ed43308370f4576b59947c",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Agile",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 282",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 282",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 282,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "The multiple attack penalty you take with this weapon on the second attack on your turn is \u20134 instead of \u20135, and \u20138 instead of \u201310 on the third and subsequent attacks in the turn.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 172,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "36bd7375ee334ca30404dac02062c504",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "links": [
          {
            "alt": "off-guard",
            "aonid": 58,
            "game-obj": "Conditions",
            "name": "off-guard",
            "type": "link"
          }
        ],
        "name": "Backstabber",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 282",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 282",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 282,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "When you hit an off-guard creature, this weapon deals 1 precision damage in addition to its normal damage. The precision damage increases to 2 if the weapon is a _+3 weapon_.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 174,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "c0d76f25881949145ec6769d79ad49b5",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Deadly",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 282",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 282",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 282,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "On a critical hit, the weapon adds a weapon damage die of the listed size. Roll this after doubling the weapon\u2019s damage. This increases to two dice if the weapon has a _greater striking rune_ and three dice if the weapon has a _major striking rune_. For instance, a rapier with a _greater striking rune_ deals 2d8 extra piercing damage on a critical hit. An ability that changes the size of the weapon\u2019s normal damage dice doesn\u2019t change the size of its deadly die.",
        "type": "trait",
        "value": "d8"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 179,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "6a57956799f3d30121d529e48f12904c",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Finesse",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 282",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 282",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 282,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "You can use your Dexterity modifier instead of your Strength modifier on attack rolls using this melee weapon. You still calculate damage using Strength.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 184,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "f04b0f8de1f6fd2a5c1ab77926c70244",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Grapple",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 282",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 282",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 282,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "You can use this weapon to Grapple with the Athletics skill even if you don\u2019t have a free hand. This uses the weapon\u2019s reach (if different from your own) and adds the weapon\u2019s item bonus to attack rolls as an item bonus to the Athletics check. If you critically fail a check to Grapple using the weapon, you can drop the weapon to take the effects of a failure instead of a critical failure.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 224,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
